    <text type="letter"> 
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc.03088.001_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place"><handShift rend="printed"/>PAN-REPUBLIC CONGRESS COMMITTEE.<ptr target="loc.03088_n7"/></name>
                    <name type="place">OFFICE OF SECRETARY AND TREASURER, 20 SPRUCE STREET.<ptr target="loc.03088_n1"/></name>
                    <name type="place">WM. H. ARNOUX, Chairman.</name>
                    <name type="place">WM. O. MCDOWELL, Secretary.</name>
                    <name type="place">NEWARK, N.J.,</name> 
                    <date when="1891-08-21"><handShift rend="manuscript"/>Aug 21<hi rend="underline">st</hi> <handShift rend="printed"/>1891.</date>
                </dateline>
                <handShift rend="manuscript"/>
                <salute>"Walt Whitman"</salute>
                <salute>My dear Sir</salute> 
            </opener>
            <p>On Oct 12th (Discovery day<ptr target="loc.03088_n2"/> falls this year on Sunday) our Pan Republic Congress 
                organizing government in Independence Hall<ptr target="loc.03088_n3"/> 
                Phil to adopt and added to all peoples
                and to organize the Human Freedom League<ptr target="loc.03088_n4"/>
                In the evening we have a public meeting in the Academy of Music<ptr target="loc.03088_n5"/>
                The time, the place, the work are
                all suggestive and is it to be wondered at that our 
                Comt turn to you for the poem of the occasion.</p>
            <closer>
                <salute>Hoping that you will favor us I am</salute>
                <salute>Very truly yours</salute>
                <signed><hi rend="underline">W O McDowell</hi></signed>
            </closer>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc.03088.002_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
            <pb xml:id="leaf002r" facs="loc.03088.003_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <pb xml:id="leaf002v" facs="loc.03088.004_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
            <note type="editorial" place="back" resp="#ht">The Enclosed letter settles many things ahead of 
            <unclear reason="illegible" resp="#cn" cert="low">elaborate publicity</unclear></note>
            <note type="editorial" place="bottom" resp="#ht">see notes Dec 14 1891</note>
